{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PPLFNyrVUrNnjaL8BB1LxL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No plugins installed in the directory. I need to install `repository-s3` on all nodes. This requires restarting the pods.\n\nActually, let me think more carefully. In Elasticsearch 8.x, can I install a plugin without restarting? No, plugins require a restart.\n\nBut wait - in the official `elasticsearch:8.11.1` Docker image, can I run `elasticsearch-plugin install repository-s3` and then the pod will have it? The problem is that once the pod is restarted, it will reset to the original image unless the plugin is installed as part of the image or mounted.\nI think the best approach is to add an init container to the StatefulSet that installs the plugin before Elasticsearch starts. This will trigger a rolling restart of the pods, and once they're back up with the plugin installed, I can configure the keystore and register the repository.\n\nBut I need to clarify something first—both the `es` StatefulSet (the 3 master/data nodes) and the `es-data` StatefulSet (the 2 dedicated data nodes) will need the S3 plugin installed since they both handle snapshots. Let me verify which nodes actually require it and check if the plugin is already available in the image or if I need to install it separately.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":474,"cache_read_input_tokens":36877,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":474},"output_tokens":35,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7e554dd-6f36-41ae-9b4b-092534db1467","uuid":"515251aa-97ea-4278-b631-3a66c8219123","request_id":"req_011CcP5ydn9iiXGBsLDoWfFH"}
