{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TqaqtDZVZCHvBhAwb5UqHn","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the minio-init job failed because:\n1. There was no MinIO service (`minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000` DNS wasn't resolving)\n2. The bucket wasn't created\n\nThe job is now complete, but the bucket likely doesn't exist. I need to:\n1. Create the MinIO service\n2. Create the `es-backups` bucket in MinIO\n3. Install the `repository-s3` plugin on all Elasticsearch nodes\n4. Create the `es-secure-settings` secret with credentials\n5. Add credentials to Elasticsearch keystore on all nodes\n6. Register the snapshot repo\n7. Create the snapshot\n\nFor the S3 plugin installation, I can't just exec into a running pod and restart the process since Elasticsearch is containerized. The cleanest approach is to patch the StatefulSet with an init container that installs the plugin, though this will trigger a rolling restart of the nodes.\n\nBefore I go down that path, let me verify whether the S3 plugin is actually missing or just not initialized—the empty `_cat/plugins` response might not tell the whole story.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7318,"cache_read_input_tokens":37351,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7318},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7e554dd-6f36-41ae-9b4b-092534db1467","uuid":"427f8f26-1569-45cd-b988-30e36d75829d","request_id":"req_011CcP5zZedgQVuQHpKY52RQ"}
