{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CwzLrUp9DuGSZL7VpUn45J","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to add these credentials to the Elasticsearch keystore on ALL nodes. The nodes are:\n- es-0, es-1, es-2 (from the `es` statefulset)\n- es-data-0, es-data-1 (from the `es-data` statefulset)\n\nI'll exec into each pod and use `elasticsearch-keystore add` to add the credentials.\n\nActually, in Elasticsearch 8.x, the proper approach for keystore management in Kubernetes is:\n1. Create a secret with the keystore keys\n2. Mount the secret to the ES pod\n\nBut since the pods don't have the keystore volume mounted from a secret, I need to exec into each pod and manually add the keystore entries.\nI'm piping the MinIO credentials into the keystore add command for both the access key and secret key, then reloading the secure settings through the API without requiring a restart. I'll run this across all five nodes in parallel.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":350,"cache_read_input_tokens":47029,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":350},"output_tokens":44,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7e554dd-6f36-41ae-9b4b-092534db1467","uuid":"81276100-ff52-4f66-a5b8-642821b1d9d5","request_id":"req_011CcP63pMzp8frwbZoveAPQ"}
